## Conventions

### API Responses

All API responses use a consistent shape:

```ts
{ data, error, metadata }
```

Errors always follow:

```ts
{ code, message, details }
```

### Code Quality

- No `any`, `@ts-ignore`, or `eslint-disable` without an explanatory comment
- No business logic in entry-point handlers — handlers orchestrate, modules execute
- Named exports only (no default exports)
- `const` arrow functions preferred
- Early returns over nested conditionals
- Max function length: 30 lines
- Max file length: 200 lines

## Testing

- Run your test command after every change
- Never remove or weaken existing tests
- New features require integration tests

## Git

- Commit after each meaningful step
- Use conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`
- Never commit `.env` or any file containing secrets

## When In Doubt

- Prefer boring, explicit code over clever abstractions
- If something feels wrong, stop and ask before continuing
- Do not invent APIs or imports — check they exist first
- Leave a `// TODO:` comment rather than silently skipping something
